      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I\u0027m confused at this statement;  The cooled_by association was literally created to fulfill this Redfish property\n\nMaybe it was applied wrong in bmcweb. In PDI it is documented like this:\n\n```\ncat xyz/openbmc_project/Inventory/Item/Fan.interface.yaml\ndescription: \u003e\n    Implement to provide Fan attributes.\n\nassociations:\n    - name: cooling\n      description: \u003e\n          Objects that implement Fan can optionally implement the \u0027cooling\u0027\n          association to provide a link back to a Item.\n      reverse_name: cooled_by\n      required_endpoint_interfaces:\n          - xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item\n```\n\nThere is no mention of any chassis or resource placement.\n\nAlso the `xyz/openbmc_project/Inventory/Item/README.md` says nothing about fan resource placement. It only documents that fans can associate to inventory items.\n\nDo you know where the current usage was documented?\n\nWhy are we using \u0027cooling\u0027 type association to model redfish containment? \n\nIsn\u0027t that what \u0027containing\u0027 association is for?\n\n\u003e Are you attaching sub-items to the cooled by in your config?\n\nI\u0027m configuring associations as per EM physical topology design,\nwith adjustments made to enable fan inventory rework.\n\nUsing `containing` type association to determine location/containment and `cooling` type association to determine which chassis is enjoying the breeze!\n\nThe EM patch in gerrit topic, direct link for reference:\nhttps://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/entity-manager/+/87062",
