      "message": "\u003e Soemthing seems off with this modeling.  In the above, you\u0027d have\n\nYou\u0027re right 😊, technically there could be an extra fan box chassis- i did not model that here to keep it simple. The code should work in both cases.\n\n\u003e Just because a fan is contained with a chassis doesn\u0027t mean it cools that component, that\u0027s why Redfish separates them.\n\nYes, but currently i don\u0027t see a way to query that with bmcweb.\n\n\u003e Have you talked through any of this modeling with the DMTF specification\n or have examples?  They write the spec so they have a better handle on \nthis stuff.\n\nI went to redfish forum to clarify the preferred resource placement in my situation:\n\nhttps://redfishforum.com/thread/1276/clarification-uri-redfish-resources-inventory\n\n\nI don\u0027t think i can ask them about OpenBMC specifics though.\n\nMade a PDI review to get input for how it should look like on DBus,\nthat\u0027s also part of the gerrit topic.\n\nhttps://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/+/88235\n\nI don\u0027t have examples of other redfish implementations or how they handle it.\n\nLet me know in case you have a link/repo and i can try to start digging there.",
